>> Select two reasons why using multiple 3x3 convolutions is more efficient than a single 7x7? <<

[x] A. One can add non-linear activations between convolutions {{ selected: A. Correct}}
[ ] B. The receptive field is larger {{ selected: B. Incorrect, the size of the receptive field depends on how many 3x3 convolutions you choose to stack. If you stack two 3x3 convolutions, you will have the receptive field of a 5x5 convolution. If you stack three 3x3 convolutions, you will have the receptive field of a 7x7 convolution. If you stack four 3x3 convolutions, you will have the receptive field of a 9x9 convolution, and so on.}}  
[x] C. There are fewer parameters for the same receptive field {{ selected: C. Correct }}
[ ] D. It has fewer operations {{ selected: D. Incorrect, it has more operations}}

